1. Improving community resilience through ensuring access to clean drinking water:

1.1.1. Preparatory activities on renovation of the premises of water distribution station undertaken; [3] project estimation documents prepared;
1.1.2. Procurement and delivery of the artesian water purification equipment and reconstruction of water purification compound; [878] people received access to safe drinking water in Tazakonis community;
1.2.1. Installation of water pipelines in the Beltau Centre community; [175] people received access to safe drinking water in Beltau community center; 
1.3.1. Installation of water pipelines Mulik community; [1178] people received access to safe drinking water in Mulik community; 
1.4.1. Establishment of the “Drinking Water Association (DWA)”; [1] DWA established;
1.4.2. Training local specialists and community members on proper maintenance of the installed water system, its effective use, hygiene rules; [20] people trained on proper use of water system;
1.4.3. Implementation of WASH procedures; [150] people trained on proper sanitation and hygiene norms; [100] sanitation and hygiene materials developed.


2. Enhancing the social wellbeing of the rural population (including women/youth) through expanding income generation opportunities and promoting inclusive sustainable growth of the tourism in Karakalpakstan:

2.1.1. Implementation of the [6] new income generation projects co-financed; [70] new people directly benefited;
2.1.2. Enhancing rural entrepreneurs’ skills; [60] women and youth enhanced their skills on value chain management, strategy formulation and taxation;
2.1.3. Implementation of the new womens entrepreneurship development through provision of necessary equipment and trainings; [35] new job places created for women and girls.


3. Promoting climate change adaptation actions through evidence based afforestation initiatives:

3.1.1. Monitoring dried bottom of the Aral Sea (SIC ICWC and International Aral Sea region Innovation Center); Full set of data including GIS mapping and remote sensing, as well as physical check results available;
3.1.2. Conducting practical trainings and developing methodological guidelines; [850] (30% women) representatives of State Forestry Departments, pasture cooperative members, local farmer and dehkans enhanced their knowledge and skills on innovative methods of afforestation;
3.2.1. Provision of necessary machinery and technology to the relevant institutions (e.g. the Forestry Departments); Necessary machinery and equipment provided to Takhtakopir State Forestry Department and 3 pasture cooperatives.

